mary queen of scots is a 2013 swiss period drama directed by thomas &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; . it is his first film in english and french language starring the bilingual french actress camille rutherford . the film portrays the inner life of mary , the queen of scotland . the film is based on austrian novelist stefan zweig 's 1935 biography , mary stuart , a long-term bestseller in germany and france but out of print in the uk and the us for decades until 2010 . the film was first screened at the 2013 international film festival locarno and was later shown at the 2013 toronto international film festival .